X
Y
\lambda
\mu
E((X+Y)^2)
E[(X+Y)^2]=E[X^2]+E[Y^2]+2EXEY
2EXEY=2\lambda\mu
X\sim\mathrm{Pois}(\lambda)
 \operatorname{Var}X=\operatorname EX^2-(\operatorname EX)^2=\lambda. 
 \operatorname EX^2=\lambda+\lambda^2. 
 Es^{X+Y} = Es^XEs^Y = \sum_k  \exp(-\lambda)\frac{\lambda ^k}{k!} s^k  \sum_l \exp(-\mu)\frac{\mu^l}{l!}s^l  \\ = \exp (\lambda(s-1))\exp (\mu(s-1)) = \exp ((\lambda+\mu)(s-1)) 
 E[(X+Y)^2] = Var(X+Y) + [E(X+Y)]^2 = (\lambda+\mu) +  (\lambda+\mu)^2 
Var(X)=E[(X-\mu)^2]=E[X^2]-2E[X]\mu+\mu^2=E[X^2]-(E[X])^2
E[X^2]=Var(X)+(E[X])^2
E[X^2]=\lambda+\lambda^2
